programmes.show_description: The White Whale: Mike Barnette, Jimmy Gadomski and the team are back on a cold case - the famous disappearance of seven US Navy planes in 1945. (S2, ep 5)
Texan farm workers are confronted by a 200-foot long object in the sky in 1957. In 1979, a UFO releases spiked spheres that leave a man unconscious in Scotland. (S2, ep 7)
In Brazil, three men escape a close encounter. In Canada, a thirteen-year-old boy is blinded temporally after investigating a bizarre object. (S2, ep 8)
Giorgio Tsoukalos takes a look back at the incredible hieroglyphs, petroglyphs, and geoglyphs that he believes tell a worldwide story of alien visitation.
Raging Bulls: Desperate to cull the exploding gator population, the swampers employ new, risky tactics to target giant breeding bulls. Joey and Zak create a feeding frenzy. (S11, ep 1)
Venom Warriors: Troy, Chase and Bill go deep diving in search of pythons but may have bitten off more than they can chew. Bruce and Zak venture into Viper Jungle. (S2, ep 2)
Lawyer Up Son: The shop lands itself in trouble when a customer calls in their lawyer to settle a huge row over a fake receipt. Fortunately, Les has a trick up his sleeve. (S7, ep 10)
Join antiques expert and presenter David Dickinson as more collectors try to sell their items to dealers. Will they strike a deal or take a chance at auction instead? (S9, ep 17)
Wood Green 2: Join David Dickinson as more collectors try to sell their items to dealers. Will they strike a deal, or will they take a chance at auction instead? (S10, ep 72)
The Pickers rummage through central Saskatchewan, scoring vintage pistols, antique toys and an inflatable Coca-Cola display. (S3, ep 8)
The vintage restorers return for season four, challenging themselves to make money out of other people's automotive junk and classic collectables. (S4, ep 4)
Reign or Shine: King Darrell strives to defend his throne, but Rene and Casey signal their intentions to undermine his plans. Meanwhile, Kenny gets bowled over by his locker. (S14, ep 9)
The King of Montebowl-o: Barry turns up to auction armed with a present for a certain hustler. Meanwhile, Brandi and Bozek get a firm grip on a smaller unit. (S14, ep 10)
Oh Yes He Did: Ashley is pulled into the fray as Seth's plan to sell the Pontiac shop hits a snag. Then a meeting with a buyer leaves them in a life-changing situation. (S7, ep 13)
Family Matters: Finding it hard to forgive Seth for trying to sell his business, Les locks himself in his office. Meanwhile, a fight breaks out on the pawn shop floor. (S8, ep 1)
Rick Vs. The Globe Of Death: Rick and Chum get a genius package containing letters signed by Albert Einstein. Chum and Corey marvel at replicas of Thor's helmet and hammer.
Return To Froggy Bayou: Joey and Zak stake out game trails to nab deer-eating gators, while Daniel and Big Tee get creative with their bait. (S11, ep 2)
Skunk Ape Alley: The war against pythons invading the Everglades begins as Troy Landry, his son Chase and snake expert Bill uncover the sepents' breeding grounds. (S2, ep 1)

Beastly Howls, Holloman Air Force Base UFO, and the Cabin That Defies Gravity: How does a cabin seemingly defy gravity? And what is the origin of some frightening howls? (S4, ep 5)
Submerged: A Turkish drought reveals a long-lost Basilica and its secrets, while the hull of a ship in the North Sea answers decades-old questions. (S1, ep 4)

What Lies Below: UAPs have been seen entering the ocean at high speeds - and since our oceans can be as deep as six miles, were the UAPs simply trying to get home? (S1, ep 9)
